%section
  %h2 Where I'm coming from
  %ul
    %li.fragment No MLS
    %li.fragment MS's in Computer Science and Instructional Technology
  %h2{:style=>"margin-top: 1em"} Assertions
  %ul
    %li.fragment Metadata is useful insofar as it makes things discoverable.
    %li.fragment Common things should be easy; hard things should be possible.
    %li.fragment Free-text metadata makes search hard, has huge opportunity cost
    %li.fragment Incorrect data is rare but problematic
    %li.fragment Library "standards" are often dumb and routinely ignored

%section
  %h2 What we'll cover in the next four minutes
  %ol
