%section
  %h2 1. The data are bad
  %div
    %strong "Bad"
    means
    %em incorrect
    OR
    %em inconsistent
    OR
    %em otherwise hard for a computer to deal with
  %ul.fragment
    %li "Unique" identifiers aren't unique
    %li "Standards" aren't standard
    %li "Local practice" doesn't help when there's no more "local"
    %li.red We're not printing cards anymore!

%section
  %h2 More than 5mn worth. But briefly:
  %div The problem is death by a thousand cuts
  %ul
    %li 6500 '020a' subfields with no ISBN in them; 8500 fail checksum
    %li 30k records with invalid 008 fields
    %li Punctuation overloaded with syntactic and sematic meaning? Really??
    %li Q: How many LCSH headings should include these "words":
    %ul
      %li Unitd
      %li Germay
      %li Austrlia
      %li Libaries
    %li Did you know we put E-ISSNs in the 022y (reserved for incorrect ISSNs)?


%section
  %h2 Things to consider
  %ul
    %li.fragment Typos render things invisible (and you can't browse an increasing percentage of stuff)
    %li.fragment We're not far from "our" data being used primarily outside of "our" systems.
    %li.fragment Things will only be cataloged once. Don't throw away data!
    %li.fragment Thinking about serials too hard will give you night terrors.

